ZH: 山顶上有一座著名的攀岩区。
EN: There is a famous rock climbing area at the top of the mountain.

ZH: 他们在峭壁上攀爬了几个小时。
EN: They climbed the cliff for several hours.

ZH: 攀登珠穆朗玛峰对身体和心理的挑战很大。
EN: Climbing Mount Everest is a great physical and mental challenge.

ZH: 那个登山者用绳子攀爬峭壁。
EN: The mountaineer used ropes to climb the steep cliff.

ZH: 他们都非常训练有素，能轻易攀爬悬崖峭壁。
EN: They are all well-trained and can easily scale cliffs.

ZH: 我们看到一只猴子在树上攀爬。
EN: We saw a monkey climbing up a tree.

ZH: 攀登海拔8000米的山峰是一个巨大的挑战。
EN: Climbing a mountain peak at an altitude of 8000 meters is a huge challenge.

ZH: 他们利用冰斧攀登冰壁。
EN: They used ice axes to climb the icy wall.

ZH: 攀登过程中需要非常顽强的毅力。
EN: Climbing requires great perseverance.

ZH: 那个登山者攀爬到了峰顶。
EN: The mountaineer climbed to the summit.

ZH: 他是一位经验丰富的攀岩教练。
EN: He is an experienced rock climbing instructor.

ZH: 他正在攀登职业生涯的顶峰。
EN: He is climbing to the peak of his career.

ZH: 每年都有很多人梦想攀登珠穆朗玛峰。
EN: Many people dream of climbing Mount Everest every year.

ZH: 这位登山者专注于攀登世界上最高的山峰。
EN: The mountaineer is focused on climbing the tallest peaks in the world.

ZH: 他们的目标是攀登七大洲的最高山峰。
EN: Their goal is to climb the highest peaks on all seven continents.

ZH: 攀岩需要很好的身体平衡和灵活性。
EN: Rock climbing requires good physical balance and flexibility.

ZH: 他筹备了很长时间才敢攀登冰瀑。
EN: He prepared for a long time before daring to climb the ice waterfall.

ZH: 这座山峰因为难度极高而被称为攀岩者的天堂。
EN: This mountain peak is known as a paradise for climbers because of its extreme difficulty.

ZH: 攀岩是一项具有很高风险的运动。
EN: Rock climbing is a high-risk sport.

ZH: 只有强壮和有经验的登山者才能攀登这座陡峭的山峰。
EN: Only strong and experienced mountaineers can climb this steep peak.
